an class=3D"ph mtbcommand">One-Way
		ANOVA</span></h1><div class=3D"promo"><a target=3D"_blank" href=3D"https:=
//www.minitab.com/products/minitab/">Learn more about Minitab </a></div></d=
iv></div></div><div class=3D"frame"><div class=3D"inner"><div class=3D"body=
 taskbody mtbtaskbody topicbody1">=20
<div class=3D"section context">=20
<p class=3D"p"> A chemical engineer wants to compare the hardness of four b=
lends of paint. Six samples of each paint blend were applied to a piece of =
metal. The pieces of metal were cured. Then each sample was measured for ha=
rdness. In order to test for the equality of means and to assess the differ=
ences between pairs of means, the analyst uses one-way ANOVA with multiple =
comparisons. </p></div>=20
<ol class=3D"ol steps">=20
<li class=3D"li step"><span class=3D"ph cmd">Open the sample data, <a rel=
=3D"nofollow" href=3D"https://support.minitab.com/en-us/minitab/media/gener=
ated-content/datasets/PaintHardness.MWX">PaintHardness.MWX</a>.</span></li>
=20
<li class=3D"li step"><span class=3D"ph cmd">Choose <span class=3D"ph"><spa=
n class=3D"ph menucascade"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol - current ">Stat</sp=
an><abbr title=3D"and then"> &gt; </abbr><span class=3D"ph uicontrol - curr=
ent ">ANOVA</span><abbr title=3D"and then"> &gt; </abbr><span class=3D"ph u=
icontrol - current ">One-Way</span></span></span>.</span></li>
=20
<li class=3D"li step"><span class=3D"ph cmd">Select <span class=3D"ph uicon=
trol - current ">Response data are in one column for all factor levels</spa=
n>.</span></li>
=20
<li class=3D"li step"><span class=3D"ph cmd">In <span class=3D"ph uicontrol=
 - current ">Response</span>, enter <span class=3D"ph dataset_columnname">H=
ardness</span>. </span></li>
=20
<li class=3D"li step"><span class=3D"ph cmd">In <span class=3D"ph uicontrol=
 - current ">Factor</span>, enter <span class=3D"ph dataset_columnname">Pai=
nt</span>. </span></li>
=20
<li class=3D"li step"><span class=3D"ph cmd">Click the <span class=3D"ph ui=
control - current ">Comparisons</span> button, then select <span class=3D"p=
h uicontrol - current ">Tukey</span>.</span></li>
=20
<li class=3D"li step"><span class=3D"ph cmd">Click <span class=3D"ph uicont=
rol - current ">OK</span> in each dialog box.</span></li>
</ol>=20
<div class=3D"example"><h2 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Interpret the resul=
ts</h2>=20
=20
<p class=3D"p">The p-value for the paint hardness ANOVA is less than 0.05. =
This result indicates that the hardness of the paint blends differs signifi=
cantly. The engineer knows that some of the group means are different.</p>=
=20
<p class=3D"p"> The engineer uses the Tukey comparison results to formally =
test whether the difference between a pair of groups is statistically signi=
ficant. The graph that includes the Tukey simultaneous confidence intervals=
 show that the confidence interval for the difference between the means of =
Blend 2 and 4 is 3.114 to 15.886. This range does not include zero, which i=
ndicates that the difference between these means is significant. The engine=
er can use this estimate of the difference to determine whether the differe=
nce is practically significant.</p>=20
<p class=3D"p">The confidence intervals for the remaining pairs of means al=
l include zero, which indicates that the differences are not significant. <=
/p>=20
    <p class=3D"p">The low predicted R<sup class=3D"ph sup">2</sup> (24.32%=
) value indicates that the model generates imprecise predictions for new ob=
servations. The imprecision may be due to the small size of the groups. Thu=
s, the engineer should not use the model to make generalizations beyond the=
 sample data.</p>
